						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I have two RF boxes (the gray things) which I can test with. One is from top-loader NES, and one from my front-loader NES. The one I'm using in the video is from my top-loader NES.</div><br />I have at lest 3 or 4 of them, one of them from my NTSC NES, and as far I know they are all strictly identical. The only difference is the antenna connector is slightly different mechanically, but the inside of the RF switch is the exact same, and since I don't use an antenna for TV I could use the &quot;NTSC&quot; or &quot;PAL&quot; one interchangeability (it's probably wrong to call them NTSC or PAL though).</div>

